Sentencas: Time-dependent events during operation of SOFCs, i.e., performance enhancement and/or deterioration, can be readily observed for the cell composed of strontium-doped lanthanum manganite (LSM) cathode and yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte, concomitant with the change in interfacial structure of LSM/YSZ.
Titulo: Influence of (La,Sr)MnO3+δ cathode composition on cathode/electrolyte interfacial structure during long-term operation of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The influence of LSM composition on the electrochemical properties and microstructure of LSM/YSZ interface during prolonged operation was investigated.
Titulo: Influence of (La,Sr)MnO3+δ cathode composition on cathode/electrolyte interfacial structure during long-term operation of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Four different LSM cathodes were used and the change in microstructure, especially TPB-length, was evaluated quantitatively by a focused ion beam scanning electron microscope (FIB-SEM).
Titulo: Influence of (La,Sr)MnO3+δ cathode composition on cathode/electrolyte interfacial structure during long-term operation of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For LSM cathodes with A-site deficient compositions, the change in TPB-length had a minor contribution to the performance enhancement after 20 h of galvanostatic operation.
Titulo: Influence of (La,Sr)MnO3+δ cathode composition on cathode/electrolyte interfacial structure during long-term operation of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: On the other hand, for 100 h duration an increase in cathode overpotential was confirmed, accompanied with the formation of thin layer of LSM over YSZ electrolyte.
Titulo: Influence of (La,Sr)MnO3+δ cathode composition on cathode/electrolyte interfacial structure during long-term operation of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A series of phenomena were triggered by the change in oxygen nonstoichiometry of LSM under polarized states.
Titulo: Influence of (La,Sr)MnO3+δ cathode composition on cathode/electrolyte interfacial structure during long-term operation of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The mechanism for microstructural change was proposed and the long-term stability of LSM/YSZ interface was discussed.
Titulo: Influence of (La,Sr)MnO3+δ cathode composition on cathode/electrolyte interfacial structure during long-term operation of solid oxide fuel cells
